Few hours after they were sacked by Ondo State governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, the deputy governor, Hon. Agboola Ajayi,  has reappointed  all his sacked aides, just as the plot to impeach him  thickens. The aides affected include Olomu Bayo, Special Assistant, Special Duties, Olawale Abolade Mukaila, Special Assistant on Photography, Babatope Okeowo (Deputy Chief Press Secretary),  Samuel Ogunmusi,Personal Assistant, (Deputy Governor), Omotunmise Tokunbo, SpecialAssistant to the wife of the Deputy Governor  and Mrs Erifeyiwa Shola Akinnugba, Special Assistant on Photography, wife of the Deputy Governor. The governor, in a statement by his chief press secretary, Segun Ajiboye, said the affected aides are to submit all government’sproperty in their possession to the Chief of Staff to the Governor. However, the new twist is not unconnected to the defection of the deputy governor from the All Progressives Congress (APC) to Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) at his Kiribo hometown on Sunday. Ajayi had maintained that he remains the deputy governor of the state  after his official resignation from the APC.